- 'caught the biggest wave of consumer interest' refers to the product with the highest sales amount;
- 'ocean of spirits' is a metaphor for the Alcohol category;
- 'total sales amount' refers to the metric used to measure consumer interest.

- 'bustling harbor' refers to a location with high activity;
- 'ships' is a metaphor for sales;
- 'gold coins' is a metaphor for currency value, representing the total amount and unit price;
- 'dozen' refers to more than 10 sales;
- '2022' specifies the year of the sales period.

- 'main store' refers to the location with location_id = 1;
- 'holiday season' is considered the period from December 1, 2021, to March 31, 2022;
- 'sales champion' refers to the employee who achieves the highest number of sales during the specified time.
